-- Czechs Expect Taxed CO2 Credits to Be Worth About $22, Hospodarske Reports
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-10-22T04:55:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/czechs-expect-taxed-co2-credits-to-be-worth-czk385-hospodarske-reports.html
The Czech government, which plans to
impose a 25 percent tax on carbon dioxide allowances in the next
two years, estimates each credit will be worth 385 koruna ($22),
Hospodarske Noviny reported, citing persons present at the
government meeting where the decision was made.  The government decided to tax the credits to compensate for
subsidies to solar power producers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  